Following the GOP's defeat in the 06 mid-term Elections, an Opinion piece published on [[November 19]], [[2006]] by [[Joshua Muravchik]], a leading [[neoconservatism|neoconservative]] and a resident scholar at the conservative view [[American Enterprise Institute]], titled BOMB IRAN shocked some readers, with its hawkish overtures in support of more unilateral action by the United States, this time against Iran.<ref>
